Prerequisites
  Node.js (v14 or above recommended)
  npm (Node package manager)
Installation
  1. Clone the repository or download the code.
        git clone https://github.com/yourusername/express-jwt-auth-api.git
        cd express-jwt-auth-api
  2. Install the required dependencies.
        npm install
Running the Server
  To start the server, run:
      node app.js
The server will start on port 5000. You can access it at http://localhost:5000.
API Endpoints
  1. Get Message
      Endpoint: GET /
      Description: Returns a simple message.

  2. Response:
      "message": "a simple api"
  3. Access Profile
      Endpoint: POST /profile
      
      Description: Accesses the user's profile if a valid JWT is provided.
      
      Headers:
        Authorization: Bearer <token>
      Response:
        If the token is valid:
        {
            "message": "profile accessed",
            "authData": {
                "user": {
                    "id": 1,
                    "username": "anish",
                    "email": "anish@gmail.com"
                },
                "iat": 1599999999,
                "exp": 1600000299
            }
        }
        If the token is invalid:
        {
          "result": "invalid token!"
        }
Middleware
  verifyToken
  This middleware function verifies the JWT provided in the Authorization header of the request. If the token is valid, it allows the request to proceed; otherwise, it returns an error.
